			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">And note that the General regens real fast: even if he gets hit quite hard he'll be at 100% for the next encounter. He's not a PC warrior <img src="images/smiles/icon_smile.gif" alt="Smile" border="0" />.
<br />

<br />
At 59 with competent players, three groups should be easy: the mobs aren't very tough by PoP standards and we've even done it with a 65 Beastie as main tank rather than a plate class. The only real problem is that they come in packs, so it's good to have several tank/healer pairs to tank the adds while everyone else piles in to assist the main tank. If you don't have enough players a high level Mage or Beastlord can probably pet-tank adds OK or a Druid, Necro or Ranger can kite them until you're ready to finish them off.
<br />

<br />
Also, be careful of line of sight attacks: we have had a Ranger accidentally hit the General with an arrow that was aimed at a mob and aggro him, then had to mem-blur the General to stop him attacking. A Mage nuke that hit him by mistake could lead to a real bad day <img src="images/smiles/icon_smile.gif" alt="Smile" border="0" />. 
<br />

<br />
Pets have occasionally aggroed him too, though I've no idea why... again, killing the pet and mem-blur worked fine.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
